storyInfo: During a rescue mission, Absinthe finds herself trapped in a cave-in and must work with Rosa to escape. Unexpectedly, she finds herself confronting the truth behind her partner's seemingly strong convictions.

attributes.content: Underground Ruins
This is... Rhodes Island Operator...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Repeat... This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe... and Operator Rosa.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: About two and a half hours ago, we got separated from our team during a Catastrophe evacuation in the Ursine borderlands and fell into a sinkhole...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Currently, we have no casualties. The coordinates of our last position are...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Do you read me? Come in.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I still can't reach anyone.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Maybe I should try another spot—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: What are you doing standing up?
You should sit down and rest. Your leg...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Natalya.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You've been gone thirty minutes. Have you found anything?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Unfortunately, no. I haven't found anything that will help us out of here.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: But you're right. It's a naturally-formed karst cave further in. The light is shining down from above on a much deeper part of the hole, and not in a straight line.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: We can't leave through the cave, and the opening above is too far up. We probably won't be able to escape without help.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Sounds like it's more or less the same situation as here. Okay, thanks for checking.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No need to thank me!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: On the contrary, I should be thanking you.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: That reminds me, Absinthe, are you feeling better? How is your wound?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I learned some first-aid procedures when I worked in the Logistics Department. I can check if the bleeding has stopped and change your bandages.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm okay...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Don't be so quick to turn me down. You are injured because you helped me, and you guided me out of the areas affected by the aftershocks. This much is nothing.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: The east side's evacuated. No more civilians in the area!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: The last family at the bottom of the hill has gotten away. We don't have much time. We need to get out as soon as we can, or the Catastrophe—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —Watch out!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Absinthe!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Hold on tight!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Ugh... Ah.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Absinthe groans at the intense pain in her leg, but she quickly manages to bring her breathing under control and forces herself to shift her attention to her surroundings.
Her glimpse into the darkness yields no information whatsoever.
I can't see very well.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: There will be aftershocks. We need to move to a safer location.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Ugh—my light sticks aren't here... Ro... Natalya! Can you hear me?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Natalya?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Absinthe takes her hand. Her palm is still warm. Fortunately, the two of them are still together despite the fall.
However, Rosa is not responding.
Is she out?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The stench of blood... and it's sticky... She's bleeding from her head.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: A head injury...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: We need to move somewhere bright enough that I can see.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: (Lightly knocks on the fallen wall)
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: A hollow echo can be heard through the collapsed walls and beams. It causes the chaos in her head to dissipate. She closes her eyes and blinks. Slowly, her vision starts to clear.
Come on, come on... At least take me somewhere safer.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Absinthe props up her unconscious friend and starts moving in the direction of a faint glow.
I did what I was supposed to do.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Any other Rhodes Islander would've done the same. All I did was help my teammate to a space that's more structurally sound to buy ourselves time for a rescue... It's standard procedure.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Besides, like the wound on your head, my leg injury isn't serious. It's just a flesh wound, my bleeding has stopped. And I don't have any broken bones. There's no need for first aid.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Really, it's nothing.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Then... what about the comms?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I still haven't been able to reach anyone outside.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Besides, we don't have much battery left. We can't keep it turned on the whole time in hopes of catching a signal. We'll have to try again later.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Is there anything else I can do right now?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: All we can do is wait.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: If there's something you want to ask, go right ahead.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Is it that obvious?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm just wondering... the mother and child who lived at the bottom of the mountain... the ones we evacuated last... Did they really get out safely? The earthquake came so suddenly...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Also, if we really can't reach anyone, what are we going to do?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: First, before I regrouped with you, I made sure they evacuated to safety.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Second, if we can't reach anyone on our own, they'll notice we're missing when they take a head count and send a search team.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: This is all standard procedure. Just like I told you before.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Have you always been so dependable?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: What do you mean...?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You're very dependable. It's like no hardship can slow you. I don't think I'd know what to do, if I'd ended up here by myself.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm sure you'd be fine.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Why is that?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Remember Chernobog? If you really didn't know what to do, how would you have gotten out of that place, that situation, alive?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: This can't compare to that.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: How did you—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Oh, right. I forgot you're from Chernobog, too.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Of course. I did things I'm not proud of in order to survive, but I did get a lot of help from the others.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: That's exactly why I don't understand why you came back.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Care to elaborate?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You could've gotten out safely, but you chose to come back and help us evacuate the villagers who refused to leave.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Operators without search-and-rescue experience should've evacuated with the crew before the Catastrophe came instead of staying. If I wasn't able to save you, or if we don't actually make it out of this place...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Everything you did to stay alive and everything everybody did to help you will have been for nothing.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: That's true, but... if I always choose to leave, I'll always be the inexperienced rookie, won't I?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'll always be stuck in the same place, never able to help more people.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I want to be like the rest of you and do more... That's also why I chose to work out here on the front lines instead of staying with Logistics.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You can't let that push you into danger before you're ready.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You have to treasure your own life.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: (Whispers) Seriously, what would the people who helped you, even gave their lives for you, say about this...?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Care to elaborate?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Never mind.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You didn't finish. Why?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Just leave it. This isn't something I should be worrying about. I shouldn't have said anything.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: It's been some time already. Let me find another spot and try the comms again.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe and Operator Rosa. I repeat, this is Rhodes Island Operator...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Maybe hold it up higher?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm trying—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —Probe—
attributes.name: Intermittent Voice

attributes.content: —*buzz*—
attributes.name: Intermittent Voice

attributes.content: Huh?!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Hello? This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe and Operator Rosa! We got separated from our team during a Catastrophe evacuation in the Ursine borderlands and fell into a sinkhole!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Our last known position is—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —*buzz*—
attributes.name: Intermittent Voice

attributes.content: Hello? Do you read me? Our last known position is 61.700.20.450—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Hello?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Gavno! We'd finally got a signal...!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: If we got a signal, that means there are others nearby.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Let me take the communicator inside the cave. I might get a better signal where the light is shining through from above.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: The cave... Let's go together.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: But what about your injury?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I told you. I'm fine.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Given the circumstances, we should stick together.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Let's go.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Let me help you. It'll be easier on your leg...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm good.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Absinthe lightly shakes her head and avoids the hand reaching out to her.
The girl before her is strong enough to lift a massive siege weapon. Of course she could help a lightly injured Absinthe up.
Accepting her help to move forward would be the most reasonable choice right now. However, for some reason, Absinthe is unwilling to take it.
I said I'm good.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Hm, alright.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Now then, let's go.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: This way...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I found this place when I was following the edge to see if I could find a path out.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Look, a stone block that's just the right size for standing on. It'll get us a little closer to the source, although there's still some distance from the top.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: In any case, wait here for a moment. I'll simply climb up—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Be careful—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —Right! Please hand me the communicator.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Do you remember the coordinates?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Certainly, very clearly.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: But... Hm? How do I turn this on? It looks somewhat different from the ones I've used before.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Oops... I modded that one myself.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The channel's tuned. Press the rectangular button on the bottom to turn it on.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Hello?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: —*buzz*—
attributes.name: Faint Voice

attributes.content: I can hear something! Does that mean I've got a signal?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: There is definitely a signal. Now give your report like I taught you.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: A—Alright.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe and Operator Rosa. We got separated from our team during a Catastrophe evacuation in the Ursine borderlands and fell into a sinkhole...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Our last position is 61.700.20.450.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Repeat, our last position—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Hello?
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: Do you read me? This is—
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: —Catastrophe Messenger—Hello?
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: If you can hear them, say yes, and repeat the coordinates.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Yes, we can hear you! This is Rhodes Island Operators Absinthe and Rosa. We need assistance. Our last known position is 61.700.20.450!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: —Roger—
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: Stay where—
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: —Wait—
attributes.name: Fuzzy Voice

attributes.content: I... Sorry, I couldn't hear what he said in the end.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: It's okay.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: As long as you gave them the coordinates, you're halfway there.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: We should head back to where we were. It's more structurally sound there. The two aftershocks didn't damage it much. It'll be safer for us to wait for rescue.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The transmission got cut off again. The Catastrophe likely hasn't passed.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The most important thing right now is to make sure we're safe until the rescue team gets here.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Judging by the time, they should be here soon. I left a marker where we first stopped.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Do you see a red cloth?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I don't, but I have two light sticks here. Let's light them up.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Give me one.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: What's wrong?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: No, we'll save it for later. We don't know when exactly the rescue will get here. Let's not use up our resources before then.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: And I remember it should be around here...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: What...?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —Aftershock! Gavno!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Absinthe, you—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Stay there! Get down, and put your hands on the back of your head!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Do it!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Ugh...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: *cough*!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The damage isn't serious, but...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: It blocked off the light source. The pipes and beams probably didn't get damaged any—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Natalya?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Natalya, what's wrong? Can you hear me?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The only response she gets is the settling dust and the sound of someone's slowly intensifying breathing.
*huff*...
*whimper*...
Hey, I can hear you. Here, give me your hand.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Oh, you're holding a light stick. That's good.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: In the faint glow, Absinthe sees the other girl still bracing herself, curled up not too far away.
\nThere is some rubble and dust on her back, but she is apparently unwounded.
\nThe wailing just now could not have been her.
\n...Right?

attributes.content: Ugh... Ahhh...!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Natalya!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Wow, you're shaking a lot. Where are you hurt?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I can help you—ugh—the rescuers will be here soon. Hang in there!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: —Kill me—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Just kill me!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Does it... does it hurt that bad? Why would you say that?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Please... I beg you... help me...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I need to know where you're hurt to help you, but you keep avoiding me. I can't—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: *whimper*...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Natalya.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Absinthe grabs and holds the girl curled up on the ground. Finally, the girl lets go of her head and raises it to stare up into the darkness.
\nWhat is going on with her? A large number of questions are bombarding Absinthe's brain.

attributes.content: What's...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: ...wrong?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I... No... No—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Please... I beg you... Don't leave me here...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I won't leave you behind. Ever.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: So, tell me—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: If you don't tell me anything, how am I supposed to help you?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I can't see. I can't see!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I can't see anything...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You can't see...? Are your eyes hurt? Or maybe your head? Is there a blood clot pressing against your nerves?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Stay still and don't move. I need to see—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.text: The girl keeps murmuring deliriously. There are no reflections of anyone in her eyes. It is easily noticeable if Absinthe raises the light stick to take a better look.

attributes.content: Your eyes don't look like they're focusing, but there don't seem to be any new wounds on your head...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Are you hurt anywhere else? What caused this?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Slow down. Tell me as clearly as you can.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: No? Why not?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Look at what I'm saying...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I think...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Maybe you should just kill me.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Kill me...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Why do you keep saying that?!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Absinthe takes a harsh step back. The dust trembles violently in the air, just like her emotions.

attributes.content: Was everything... everything we talked about a lie?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Yes...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You said you wanted to live and help even more people. That was a lie?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Yes, it was!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: So kill me already! The same way you set that fire!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Rather than suffering through life like this, I'd rather die a quick death. Just like the people who died because of me. They...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: They wouldn't want me to live. You don't need me to live either, do you?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Just take that axe of yours and give me a good chop right here...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.text: Absinthe watches the girl forcefully slide her hand across her neck. She cannot stop her in time, and the light is too dim for her to check if the girl is hurt.

attributes.content: Just like that. It'll be quick.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.text: Absinthe doesn't understand any of this. She thinks she can hear something slowly fracturing, even if that's practically impossible in this moment.
\nThere is nobody else here. The fracture could only form between the two of them.
\nAmid the silence, Absinthe walks up to Rosa and sits her upright.

attributes.content: Phew...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I ask only this one thing.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: And you won't even grant me that?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I don't know...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I don't know what's going on with you, but I heard what you said, and I can't pretend I didn't.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Your life isn't yours alone, and neither is mine.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Her sanity keeps her from saying what she wants to say. However, the very next second, she casts her sanity aside.

attributes.content: Our lives belong to those who are forever left behind.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I'm begging you...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Too many people died in Chernobog. Did you ever read the after-action report? I did. Even though I could never count all the tiny names written on that list, I still counted them over and over...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I found Uncle Valery's name, and... I found my father's name.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: He went to Peterheim, and he lost his life there.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I don't know what exactly happened. I could only guess and keep watching Peterheim survivors like you, to try to get an answer... to...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: What are you...?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: ...to what exactly my father gave his life for. What was there in you that was worthy of his sacrifice?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I want to know. I need to know...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: But I don't have an answer! I haven't been able to find it—that's why I was going to give up, until you—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Until you moved from Logistics to the front lines and showed up on a mission like this, all of a sudden...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I thought you'd begun to move forward, but have you, actually?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: No. You haven't.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Kill me...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Enough of that! I'm not going to kill you! If you've made your choice, then how come you—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: How come you still don't cherish your life?!
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I'm begging you...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: If you really want to die, then fine. After we get out of here, when no one is looking, you'll have lots of ways to go about it—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Kill me, Sonya.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: —Suit yourself...?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Just... kill me.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Don't... Don't leave me alive in this place...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: There's... nothing here.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: 'Sonya...'
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: That's not my name. Where—
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Where do you think you are right now? Chernobog? Peterheim?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Absinthe finally understands everything. She keeps quiet, and snaps the last light stick to activate it. Then, she asks a question that will go unanswered.

attributes.content: If... If you haven't gotten over your trauma, why did you apply to come to the front lines and put yourself in danger?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Couldn't you have guessed...?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: ...that things might get this ugly?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Absinthe grasps Rosa's arm. She squeezes tightly, and then as tight as she can to burn the heat of her palm in.
\nThanks to this sudden, painful grasp, the panicking girl suffers an intense jerk.
\nShe blinks.

attributes.content: ...Where...?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: ...Where am I?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Is this what the school cafeteria... looked like?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: No, I don't remem—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: You're not in Chernobog anymore.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Where am I? Who are you?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You are somewhere underground. I'm Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Underground? Why?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Because you want to save more people.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Right now, we need to find a way out of this place. If you can hear me, close your eyes and follow me. Take a deep breath.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: I'll get you out of here.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.text: Absinthe takes a deep breath and answers as such.
\nAt first, the panicking girl does not understand the meaning behind this action, but after Absinthe repeats it again and again—
\nFinally, she slowly starts to move.

attributes.content: Phew...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: *huff*...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: *phew*...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.text: In that small space, the sound of their breathing is deafening.

attributes.content: Huff—Ugh—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*!
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: How are you feeling now?
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Uhh... Absinthe...?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: What... happened to me?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Was I crying? Why...? I'm so sorry about that...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: It's okay. It only took a little time. We should try contacting the outside again.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe and Operator Rosa. Our last position is 61.700.20.450.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Repeat... This is Rhodes Island Operator Absinthe and Operator Rosa.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Huh? There seems to be a transmission coming in—
Hello? Hello?
This is the Rhodes Island Catastrophe Rescue Team. Please report your coordinates—
We got through...
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Our last known position is 61.700.20.450. I recommend checking the fallen plate to the west.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: There are two of us. We're... hanging in there.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Na... Rosa, knock on the steel pipe next to you, use the beat I taught you before.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Two light knocks, one heavy one... Like this?
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: The coordinates and the rescue signal we got earlier are a match... The infrared detector shows... Th—They're close by!
—Hello? Can you hear us?
If you can hear us, use the frequency just now and knock on the steel pipe to answer us—
Help has arrived.
Absinthe looks up to the source of the voice, as Rosa continues to knock on the steel pipe repeatedly.
There's someone here! Right around the coordinates we got! Should be them—
Hold on, we'll get you two out right away. Stay put and don't move...
If you read me, knock on the pipe!
(Knocks)
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Okay, okay.
Hold on—
*huff*...
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: You're hurt. You should get rescued first.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm in better shape. I'll be fine.
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: Okay.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Even though she has long known that the joy of surviving a precarious situation is not nearly as intense as the books make it out to be, Absinthe nonetheless feels a sense of bewilderment.
Below clouds spreading through the skies like wildfire, she takes in the fleeting emotions like a breath.
Confirming Operator Absinthe's condition... Initial Diagnosis: Minor injuries. Rescue successful.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Please rest up and don't do anything strenuous. Once we rescue Operator Rosa, we'll help you with your leg—
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: —Operator Absinthe?
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Let me help.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: What? You shouldn't be movin—
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Oh.
attributes.name: Medic Operator

attributes.content: Huh? Absinthe? Your injury—
attributes.name: Rosa

attributes.content: I'm fine.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Give me your hand. I'll pull you up.
attributes.name: Absinthe

attributes.content: Operator Rosa.
attributes.name: Absinthe
